The face match endpoint is used to match a face to a profile on the system. Send a picture of the face along with id of the person you’d like to match.  The endpoint will attempt to match the generated embedding against every embedding stored for the profile. Return the score and result for every embedding for that profile.  You can supply the threshold to be used. If no threshold is supplied, the api will default to a threshold of 0.5.
